---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Troubleshooting — Scribe ESO Addon Manager"
  description="Fix common Scribe issues: addon not loading, path detection problems, update errors, macOS Gatekeeper, Windows SmartScreen."
  breadcrumb={[{ label: 'Guides', href: '#' }, { label: 'Troubleshooting', href: '/troubleshooting' }]}
>
  <div class="page">
    <div class="page__inner">
      <h1>Troubleshooting</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Things go wrong? Here's the fixes for the usual suspects.</p>

      <h2>Scribe can't find my AddOns folder</h2>
      <p>Scribe auto-detects the default path. If it can't:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Make sure ESO is installed and has been launched at least once — that's what creates the AddOns folder</li>
        <li>Check the default path:
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Windows:</strong> <code>C:\Users\You\Documents\Elder Scrolls Online\live\AddOns</code></li>
            <li><strong>macOS:</strong> <code>~/Documents/Elder Scrolls Online/live/AddOns</code></li>
            <li><strong>Linux (Proton):</strong> Somewhere inside <code>steamapps/compatdata/.../pfx/drive_c/users/steamuser/Documents/Elder Scrolls Online/live/AddOns</code></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Set it manually in settings</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Addon installed but not showing up in ESO</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Check the "Installed" tab in Scribe — is it actually there?</li>
        <li>Verify the files landed in the right AddOns folder</li>
        <li>Some addons need dependencies. Check if any are listed as missing</li>
        <li>Restart ESO completely — it won't pick up addon changes while running</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Addon update fails</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Check your connection</li>
        <li>The addon source might be down temporarily — try again in a bit</li>
        <li>If it keeps failing, uninstall and reinstall the addon</li>
        <li>Still broken? <a href="https://github.com/KelpHect/Scribe/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">File an issue</a> with the addon name and the error</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Scribe won't open on macOS</h2>
      <p>Gatekeeper blocks unsigned apps. Get past it:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Right-click (or Control-click) Scribe</li>
        <li>Pick "Open"</li>
        <li>Click "Open" in the dialog</li>
        <li>One-time thing, won't ask again</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Windows SmartScreen warning</h2>
      <p>Scribe isn't code-signed with a Microsoft cert so Windows throws a "protected your PC" warning:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Click "More info"</li>
        <li>Click "Run anyway"</li>
      </ol>
      <p>Normal for indie open-source software. You can cross-check the download on <a href="https://github.com/KelpHect/Scribe/releases" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Releases</a>.</p>

      <h2>Something else?</h2>
      <p>Open an issue on <a href="https://github.com/KelpHect/Scribe/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a> with your OS, Scribe version, steps to reproduce, and any error messages.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
